e, but it seems not.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"hoplite-core has only Kotlin/coroutines transitive dependencies and includes a built-in Java properties parser; extra format modules are optional, not required for meaningful core coverage.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No environment variables or system properties are required. Meaningful tests can use Kotlin data classes/value classes with MapPropertySource, PropsPropertySource, or .properties resources from hoplite-core itself; avoid YAML/JSON/TOML/HOCON examples unless intentionally adding the matching Hoplite format module.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The README's common YAML example requires hoplite-yaml, but that is optional format coverage rather than required setup for hoplite-core.\",\n    \"Native Image verification remains authoritative for any Kotlin 2.1 reflection metadata changes in 3.0.0.RC1.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0d0948c489caee02016a3ff0181b348190a6ca0e5df76ede8a\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2272, "output": 710, "cacheRead": 29184, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32166, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782575118255, "responseId": "resp_0d0948c489caee02016a3ff00ed1d481909b9561b747083f05"}, "toolResults": []}
